.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-3-7::.
6 different pets are kept: rabbit, hamster, mouse, horse, rat, lizard
The people use 6 different means of transport: boat, skateboard, taxi, tram, airplane, trike
 1. the owner of the mouse is on the left of the owner of the horse##1
 2. the owner of the rat is on the left or right of the person driving the airplane##3
 3. the person driving the tram is on the right of the person driving the taxi##1
 4. the owner of the rat is on the left of the person driving the taxi##1
 5. the person driving the airplane is on the left or right of the owner of the mouse##3
 6. the person driving the trike is on the right of the owner of the horse##1
 7. the owner of the rat is on the left of the owner of the hamster##1
 8. the person driving the boat is on the right of the owner of the lizard##1
 9. the person driving the airplane is the owner of the horse##1
10. the owner of the mouse is between the owner of the horse and the person driving the skateboard##2
11. the person driving the taxi is on the left or right of the owner of the rat##3

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1     |     2     |    3     |     4      |   5    |     6      |
| Pet         | lizard | mouse      | horse | rat | hamster | rabbit |
| Transport   | skateboard  | boat | airplane   | trike        | taxi   | tram |

